gomodel:SYNGO_4524  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 5 D shows synapses in the molecular layer. Many particles are seen in the presynaptic terminals. Particles are also seen in the postsynaptic terminal.\nFig. 6 A provides a quantitative analysis of the subcellular distribution of OGT with labelling of presynaptic and postsynaptic terminals.\nFig. 2 A shows an immunoblot of cerebellar lysate with anti-OGT antibody labelling a single band of 110 kDa.\n\n12/01/2021 Dnyanada: The protein is also expressed in the presynaptic terminal (linked SynGO ID: 4522).. Experimental description: Cerebellum was extirpated from Wistar rats (male, 9-11 weeks...). /p. 195" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-12" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4524" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

